    },
    {
      "overview_item_type": "essential_ideas",
      "overview_item_content_type": "html",
      "overview_item_title": "Essential Ideas",
      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "A rotation is an isometry.",
          "A rotation is a function defined by a center of rotation and a rotation angle.",
          "A rotation is a function, <math><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow><mi>c</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>’</mo></math>, that maps its input, a point <math><mi>P</mi></math>, to another location, <math><mi>P</mi><mo>’</mo></math>. A center of rotation, <math><mi>c</mi></math>, and a rotation angle, <math><mi>t</mi></math>, define this movement to a new location.",
          "The center of rotation of a pre-image and image is the intersection of the perpendicular bisectors of segments connecting corresponding vertices."
        ]
      }
    },
